I ordered chicken and broccoli off of door dash. New Apolo sent plantains. I called New Apolo immediately and politely asked if they could fix this by bringing the chicken and broccoli. They wouldn't fix their mistake. They told me to contact door dash. This may have something to do with that they closed a half hour from the time I called to ask for a fix, and they didn't want to send a delivery person back out. Or that it was easier to push my problem off on door dash rather than ask the kitchen to make another order. Either way, I'm left with plantains for dinner. A door dash credit doesn't replace a meal at 1030pm and in my opinion this was poor customer service. It would have been easy for them to send out a pint of chicken and broccoli but I guess it's easier to make it someone else's problem.

I came here after seeing a post on Facebook about Chino Latino, Chinese restaurant that serve Chinese and Spanish food together. I do agree that the food here has very good taste. Staff is very welcoming and greet you as soon as you enter. They make some signatures alcohol drinks that can't be carried out.  I placed two orders to go. Both steak, one with pork fried rice, the other with sweet plantains and the price was $25. Prices to me are on the higher end in my opinion. That's my reason why I'm giving them more like a 3 1/2 star rating. I can go to another Spanish restaurant that's closer to my home and get a much bigger combo meal for less in price then this place. Plus the food is very good there as well. Two large pieces of steak, half roasted chicken, rice and beans for $20 that combo can feed more then two adults.  I will come again because I want to try some of their signature alcohol drinks. All in all, to be honest, I gave it a try but won't be coming here that much due to prices.

I have always like this restaurant, however, my family and I went there yesterday. We noticed that the waiters kept rushing us to order the drinks and the food, while we were eating they kept stopping by the table to see, I guess, if we were finished. While some of us were still eating, they started to clear the table. At this point, we had to say something bc it became annoying, we then look up and see a sign posted on the wall that said, "Indoor dinning max time 40+ minutes only. While I understand that customers should not take extra time to lounge there, it is unfair to be rushed like we were yesterday. Dinner should be relaxing, give you a chance to enjoy your food, instead of feeling like you are in a race for time, it is annoying and not enjoyable AT ALL. It is not the customers fault that you chose such a small place of business. I don't think we will be going back there any time soon.
